  <thing id="iouHourShd" name="Hourglass of Shadows" description="Created by the demon-hag sorceress Agnok, the hourglass of shadows is a foul and cursed artifact capable of grinding goodly souls into malevolent and restless shadows. The unwieldy device weighs as much as two men and rests suspended on an iron stand fitted with pivots that allow its user to rotate a sand-filled central chamber of smoke-colored, etched glass. The foul device transforms the charred remains of mortals into shadows. To operate the device, the owner must place the ashes of the individual into the glass chamber along with a crushed onyx worth 100 gp. After the ashes have flowed through the chamber three times, the contents are emptied into a clay pot filled with grave dirt and brackish water. After 24 hours, this clay pot becomes a shadow urn. The hourglass must be carefully aligned before it can be used, which requires a DC 30 Spellcraft check.\n\n{b}Destruction{/b}\nThe hourglass of shadows is particularly vulnerable to spells with the light descriptor, and if any such spell that is cast on it renders it inoperative for one day per level of the spell. Casting sunburst on the hourglass at noon on a sunny, cloudless day instantly and permanently renders it completely nonmagical." compset="Wondrous">
